---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About this blog and its author"
>
  <h1>About</h1>

  <section>
    <p>
      Welcome to my blog. This is a minimalist space built with a retro-web aesthetic,
      focusing on clean design, fast performance, and readable content.
    </p>

    <h2>About the Site</h2>
    <p>
      This blog is built with <a href="https://astro.build">Astro</a>, a modern static site generator
      that prioritizes performance and developer experience. The design embraces simplicity with:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>ASCII bracket notation navigation</li>
      <li>Classic blue hyperlinks</li>
      <li>System fonts (zero downloads)</li>
      <li>Generous whitespace</li>
      <li>High contrast for accessibility</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Tech Stack</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Framework:</strong> Astro with TypeScript</li>
      <li><strong>Styling:</strong> Vanilla CSS</li>
      <li><strong>Content:</strong> Markdown/MDX with Content Collections</li>
      <li><strong>Features:</strong> RSS feed, tag system, reading time, table of contents</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Feel free to reach out or subscribe via <a href="/rss.xml">RSS</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  h1 {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  section {
    max-width: 65ch;
  }

  h2 {
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
  }
</style>
